What you need to know:

While Mr Odinga’s camp is betting on the BBI, the Deputy President has latched onto the “saviour” tag, packaging himself as a defender of the downtrodden.Though Mr Odinga is yet to formally announce his bid for the top job, the DP is characterising the race as between himself and the ODM party chief.The DP has also constantly opposed the March 2018 Handshake between Mr Odinga and President Kenyatta, painting it as a ploy to block his bid.